				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{cFDR}} = \Pr \left( {H_{0\left( i \right)}\left| {p_i \le P_i,p_j \le P_j} \right.} \right) = \frac{{p_i}}{{\Pr \left( {p_i \le P_i\left| {p_j \le P_j} \right.} \right)}}$$\end{document}cFDR=PrH0ipi≤Pi,pj≤Pj=piPrpi≤Pipj≤PjThe cFDR value for a SNP obtained from the above formula is the probability that the SNP is not associated with the primary phenotype, given its strength of association with the secondary phenotype. The ccFDR was obtained via taking the higher of the two cFDR values obtained for each SNP. The significance threshold chosen was cFDR (and ccFDR) ≤ 0.01.
